text: Nathaniel Levi (1830–1908) was a Liverpool born Victorian politician and businessman. He arrived at Hobson's Bay in April 1854 in the Matilda Wattenbach. Levi was prominent in the Jewish community, president of the Melbourne Hebrew Congregation in 1880–82 and 1904–05. ==References== .
